=09=09=09=09Silvio Berlusconi and his centre-right coalition won majorities=
 in both the=20
lower house and the Senate in Italy. He promised radical solutions to the=
=20
country=01,s problems=01*of which (though no promises here) his own conflic=
ts of=20
interest are one.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Berlusconi=01,s triumph, and after E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09America=01,s president, George Bush, unveiled a national energy=
 strategy. It=20
called for more coal mines, oil refineries and nuclear reactors. Critics sa=
id=20
he had neglected conservation.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Mr Bush=01,s new energy planE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The United States and Britain drafted a new resolution on sanct=
ions against=20
Iraq, to limit imports with a military use even more strictly but allowing=
=20
all others to enter freely while retaining financial control. China, France=
=20
and Russia, all critical of the current sanctions, seemed likely to support=
=20
the new plan in the UN Security Council.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Battling on
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Palestinians marked the anniversary of Israel=01,s creation wit=
h protests. Four=20
Palestinians and an Israeli woman were killed. The Israeli army came close =
to=20
admitting that it had earlier killed five Palestinian policemen in error.=
=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Giving Israel=01,s army its head=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09An Iranian airliner crashed in the country=01,s mountainous nor=
th. Iran=01,s=20
minister of transport, his two deputies and several members of parliament=
=20
were among the dead.
