=09=09=09=09Amr Musa, who has been a forceful foreign minister of Egypt, be=
came=20
secretary-general of the torpid Arab League.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09A new government of national unity in Macedonia gave ethnic-Alb=
anian rebels a=20
=01&final warning=018 to end their uprising, but was met by renewed gun bat=
tles in=20
the north of the country.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Representatives of the government and rebels in Sierra Leone si=
gned a=20
tentative agreement in Freetown. The rebels said they would disarm if the=
=20
pro-government militia did so too. They also released 198 child-soldiers an=
d=20
said more would follow.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: A pause in Sierra Leone=01,s warE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Court reports
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The execution of Timothy McVeigh, the Oklahoma City bomber, was=
 postponed=20
until June 11th when it emerged that the FBI had failed to disclose thousan=
ds=20
of pages of evidence. Louis Freeh, the bureau=01,s boss, admitted to Congre=
ss=20
that a =01&serious error=018 had been made.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: An apology to the FBIE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09General Wojciech Jaruzelski, Poland=01,s last communist leader,=
 went on trial in=20
Warsaw, accused of ordering soldiers to fire on shipyard workers in 1970,=
=20
when he was defence minister.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09An Iranian appeals court cut a ten-year sentence imposed on Akb=
ar Ganji in=20
January to six months. Mr Ganji, convicted for undermining national securit=
y,=20
is a campaigning journalist who named a former intelligence minister as bei=
ng=20
behind the murder of dissident intellectuals.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09No to violence
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Electing a regional parliament, Basque voters clobbered the sep=
aratist gunmen=20
of ETA, but snubbed Spain=01,s prime minister too by strongly supporting th=
e=20
non-violent nationalists.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: After Spain=01,s Basque election E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Talks between the EU and the most advanced applicant countries =
have been=20
postponed. Germany wants to limit movement of workers from Eastern Europe,=
=20
and Spain fears losing regional funds to the new members.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Canada=01,s opposition Alliance split. Eight of its 66 members =
of Parliament=20
called for Stockwell Day, the Alliance=01,s embattled leader, to resign, an=
d=20
said they would meet as a separate parliamentary group.
